load ../cache-prefix-append-only.maude

--- Coverage: a between-compaction turn appends and REUSES the cached prefix.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CACHE-PREFIX-APPEND-ONLY :
  prefix turnPending
  =>* prefix tail cacheHit .

--- Coverage: two turns both hit the cache and the prefix is untouched throughout.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CACHE-PREFIX-APPEND-ONLY :
  prefix turnPending turnPending
  =>* prefix tail tail cacheHit cacheHit .

--- Coverage: a due compaction rewrites the prefix once (the one deliberate bust).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CACHE-PREFIX-APPEND-ONLY :
  prefix compactDue tail
  =>* prefix prefixRewritten .

--- Bite: no between-compaction turn invalidates the cache. The RESIDUAL soup var
--- means a cacheMiss in ANY reachable state is a solution, so No solution proves
--- the prefix is never edited mid-conversation without a compaction trigger.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CACHE-PREFIX-APPEND-ONLY :
  prefix turnPending turnPending
  =>* cacheMiss RESIDUAL:Cfg .
